&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;TextRun SCXW86695365 BCX8&quot; lang=&quot;EN-US&quot; data-contrast=&quot;none&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW86695365 BCX8&quot;&gt;The National Political Advocacy Department (NPAD) works to strengthen the efforts of the ACLU at federal, state, and local levels of government. The department harnesses the political power that comes from having more than eight million members and supporters, as well as affiliates in every state. By organizing grassroots lobbying and issue campaigns using modern tactics, the ACLU&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW86695365 BCX8&quot;&gt;seeks&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW86695365 BCX8&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;to achieve change as profound in the legislative, administrative, and electoral arenas as it has&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW86695365 BCX8&quot;&gt;accomplished&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW86695365 BCX8&quot;&gt; through the courts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
